The paper discusses the design and testing of a new method for relaxing spatial invariance in neural network layers, with a focus on improving classification accuracy. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation with datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10, which are commonly used in computer vision research. The paper also discusses the potential implications of its findings for the inductive bias of convolutional neural networks, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
